          },
          "description": "Nadia has no conscious explanation for what she has done. She knows she called; she knows she postponed; she knows she is holding her father's journal. The reader has an explanation. Nadia does not. This is the story's closing irony: the woman who prided herself on logic acts entirely from feeling, and cannot see it."
